{"id":"9821","name":"App Store Marketing Tools","tagline":"Select an app from an App Store search to open its corresponding \"App Store Marketing Tools\" page.","icon":"ios14 c463140863 g59661","latest":"29000","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>I created this Shortcut largely to establish a direct translation between the user-facing App Store and Apple's new \"<a href=\"https://tools.applemediaservices.com/app-store\">App Store Marketing Tools</a>\" tool, the frontend of which notably <em>actually functions as a search tool</em> as opposed to the user-facing search function in the App Store Apps. </p>\n<p>It does so using a simple URL scheme (<code>https://tools.applemediaservices.com/app/&lt;selected app's numerical store ID&gt;</code>)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Text prompt to search the App Store</li>\n<li>Retrieves <code>Store ID</code> from selected App</li>\n<li>Appends <code>Store ID</code> at the end of <code>https://tools.applemediaservices.com/app/</code></li>\n<li>Copies the resulting URL to the clipboard</li>\n<li>Opens resulting URL in Safari</li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"mailto:davidblue@extratone.com\">Email</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/NeoYokel\">Twitter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@DavidBlue\">Mastodon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://discord.gg/0b9KQUKP858b0iZF\">Discord</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.notion.so/rotund/9fdc8e9610b34b8f991ebc148b760055?v=c170b58650c04fbdb7adc551a73d16a7\"><em>Everywhere</em></a>...</li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - July 31, 2021, 3:20 p.m.</strong></p>"}